      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin rounds</p><p>Add the <strong>potato</strong> <strong>rounds</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
